{
  "local_port": 60056,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can I get spring framework videos?",
  "response": "There are several platforms where you can find Spring Framework videos, ranging from free resources to paid courses. Here are some popular options:\n\n### **Free Resources**\n1. **YouTube**  \n   - Many educators and channels offer free Spring Framework tutorials. Some popular channels include:  \n     - `Java Brains` (by Koushik Kothagal)  \n     - `Telusko`  \n     - `AmigosCode`  \n     - `CodeWithChris`  \n   - Search for \"Spring Framework tutorial\" or \"Spring Boot tutorial\" to find relevant playlists.\n\n2. **Spring Official Channel**  \n   - The official Spring YouTube channel provides tutorials, webinars, and updates:  \n     [Spring Official YouTube Channel](https://www.youtube.com/user/SpringSourceDev)\n\n3. **FreeCodeCamp**  \n   - FreeCodeCamp offers free video tutorials on Spring Boot and related technologies on their YouTube channel:  \n     [FreeCodeCamp YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/c/Freecodecamp)\n\n4. **GeeksforGeeks**  \n   - GeeksforGeeks also provides concise video tutorials on their YouTube channel:  \n     [GeeksforGeeks YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/c/GeeksforGeeksVideos)\n\n### **Paid Courses**\n1. **Udemy**  \n   - Udemy offers comprehensive Spring Framework courses at affordable prices (often on sale). Popular courses include:  \n     - \"Spring & Hibernate for Beginners\" by Chad Darby  \n     - \"Master Microservices with Spring Boot and Spring Cloud\" by in28Minutes  \n     - \"Spring Framework 5: Beginner to Guru\" by John Thompson  \n   - Check out the platform: [Udemy Spring Courses](https://www.udemy.com/)\n\n2. **Pluralsight**  \n   - Pluralsight offers in-depth Spring Framework courses for subscribers:  \n     - \"Spring Framework: Spring Fundamentals\" by Bryan Hansen  \n     - \"Spring Boot: Efficient Development, Configuration, and Deployment\" by Dan Bunker  \n   - Visit the platform: [Pluralsight Spring Courses](https://www.pluralsight.com/)\n\n3. **Coursera**  \n   - Coursera offers Spring-related courses in collaboration with universities and institutions:  \n     - \"Building Scalable Java Microservices with Spring Boot and Spring Cloud\" by Vanderbilt University  \n   - Explore the platform: [Coursera Spring Courses](https://www.coursera.org/)\n\n4. **LinkedIn Learning**  \n   - LinkedIn Learning provides Spring Framework courses with professional certifications:  \n     - \"Spring: Framework in Depth\" by Frank P Moley III  \n     - \"Spring Boot Essential Training\" by Ketkee Aryamane  \n   - Visit the platform: [LinkedIn Learning Spring Courses](https://www.linkedin.com/learning/)\n\n### **Other Resources**\n1. **Spring Official Documentation**  \n   - While not videos, the official Spring documentation is an excellent resource for learning:  \n     [Spring Framework Documentation](https://spring.io/projects/spring-framework)\n\n2. **GitHub Repositories**  \n   - Some developers and educators share Spring projects with video tutorials. Search GitHub for \"Spring tutorial\" or \"Spring Boot example.\"\n\n3. **Tech Blogs and Websites**  \n   - Websites like Baeldung, Codecademy, and DZone often accompany tutorials with video content.\n\nChoose the platform that best fits your learning style and budget!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
